President Barack Obama has nominated Cass R. Sunstein to be the Administrator of the Office of Information and Regulatory Affairs, Office of Management and Budget. Sunstein is a distinguished constitutional scholar and has expertise in administrative law, policy, environmental law, and behavioral economics. He is considered uniquely qualified to lead the administration's regulatory reform agenda. Sunstein is a professor at Harvard Law School and has authored numerous books and articles. He has also served as a law clerk for Justice Thurgood Marshall and has worked in the U.S. Department of Justice. Sunstein's nomination has been sent to the United States Senate for confirmation.